            <title>[JCR-2119] Method to create default RepositoryConfig from just the repository directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2119</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>It would be useful to have a static method like RepositoryConfig.create(File) that would take the repository directory and expect to find the repository configuration in a &amp;quot;repository.xml&amp;quot; file inside that directory.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If the directory does not exist, it would be created. And if the repository configuration file does not exist, then it would be created from the default configuration included in Jackrabbit.</description>
